# =============================================================================
# app.py — Ghost Worker / Fraud Detection API
# Deployed on Hugging Face Spaces
#
# Endpoints:
#   GET  /health  — liveness check
#   POST /score   — upload a payroll CSV/Excel and receive a fraud analysis
#   GET  /docs    — Swagger UI (auto-generated by FastAPI)
#
# Detection pipeline:
#   1.  Parse uploaded CSV/Excel payroll file
#   2.  ★ Resolve column names to the canonical schema via a two-tier mapper:
#         Tier 1 — rapidfuzz (local, zero-latency, zero-cost fuzzy matching)
#         Tier 2 — Gemini Flash (API fallback, only for columns Tier 1 can't
#                  resolve above the confidence threshold)
#   3.  Detect scan type (PAYROLL_SCAN vs RINSE_SCAN) from mapped columns
#   4.  Normalise salary values (handle frequency variants and string formats)
#   5.  Engineer Rinse-only features (same_day_joiners, salary_roundness, etc.)
#   6.  Score each employee via an ensemble:
#         PAYROLL_SCAN → 70% XGBoost (full) + 30% Isolation Forest
#         RINSE_SCAN   → 100% XGBoost (rinse, lightweight)
#   7.  Convert raw ensemble probability to a 0–100 trust score
#   8.  Assign payment tier, risk level, and recommended action
#   9.  Build rule-based anomaly list and binary signal flags
#   10. Concurrently generate Gemini AI audit explanations for flagged employees
#   11. Return structured JSON conforming to the canonical response schema v2
#
# ── Column mapping strategy (Step 2) ─────────────────────────────────────────
#
#   The two-tier resolver runs ONCE per uploaded file on column headers only
#   (not on data rows), so it is fast and cheap regardless of file size.
#
#   Tier 1 — rapidfuzz token_sort_ratio  (LOCAL, zero API calls)
#     Handles: case differences, whitespace, underscores vs spaces, common
#     abbreviations, and minor typos (≤2–3 character edits).
#
#     Examples resolved automatically:
#       "Monthly Salary"  → monthly_salary    (case + space)
#       "montly_salary"   → monthly_salary    (typo)
#       "salaries"        → monthly_salary    (synonym in alias table)
#       "Dept"            → Department        (abbreviation in alias table)
#       "Acct Age Mths"   → Acct Age (Mths)   (punctuation dropped)
#       "days absent"     → Total Days Absent (alias table)
#
#     A match is accepted when similarity ≥ FUZZY_THRESHOLD (default 72).
#     Columns below the threshold are forwarded to Tier 2.
#
#   Tier 2 — Gemini 2.5 Flash  (API fallback, ONE call per file max)
#     Called only when Tier 1 leaves ≥1 unresolved canonical column AND
#     there are unmapped client columns that might carry that data.
#     Sends only the header strings (not data rows) — token cost is
#     negligible (~200–400 input tokens per file).
#     Fails gracefully: unresolved columns are imputed with 0.
#
#   Why not Gemini for everything?
#     • Gemini has a free-tier RPM/RPD limit; calling it per employee or per
#       file for a large batch would exhaust quota quickly.
#     • Tier 1 resolves the vast majority of real-world cases with zero latency
#       and zero cost.  Tier 2 is a safety net, not the primary path.
#
# Response schema version: 2.0
# =============================================================================

